<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-13255] Mirrormaker config property config.properties.exclude is not working as expected </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13255</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Objective - Use MM2 (kafka connect in distributed cluster) for data migration between cluster hosted in private data center and aws msk cluster.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Steps performed -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Started kafka-connect service.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Created 3 MM2 connectors (i.e. source connector, checkpoint connector and heartbeat connector). Curl commands used to create connectors are in the attached file.&#160; To exclude certain config properties while topic replication, we are using the &apos;config.properties.exclude&apos; property in the MM2 source connector.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Expected -&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Source topic &apos;dev.portlandDc.anamika.helloMsk&apos; should be successfully created in destination cluster.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Actual -&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Creation of the source topic&#160;&apos;dev.portlandDc.anamika.helloMsk&apos; in destination cluster fails with an error. Error is&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
